<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Getopts on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/getopts/</link><description>Recent content in Getopts on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/getopts/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Getopts: Invalid Option Error Fix</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-getopts-error/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/bash-getopts-error/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-getopts-invalid-option-error-fix"&gt;Bash Getopts: Invalid Option Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A bash getopts error occurs when a script receives an option that isn&amp;rsquo;t defined in the optstring.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-this-error-means"&gt;What This Error Means&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;code&gt;getopts&lt;/code&gt; parses command-line options defined in an optstring (e.g., &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;hf:v&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;). If the script receives an option not in the optstring, getopts sets &lt;code&gt;opt&lt;/code&gt; to &lt;code&gt;?&lt;/code&gt; and optionally triggers an error message.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;User passes undefined option (e.g., &lt;code&gt;-x&lt;/code&gt; when only &lt;code&gt;-h&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;-f&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;-v&lt;/code&gt; are defined)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Missing colon for required arguments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optstring doesn&amp;rsquo;t include all valid options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Not handling the &lt;code&gt;?&lt;/code&gt; case for unknown options&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="1-handle-unknown-options"&gt;1. Handle unknown options&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# WRONG: Not handling unknown options&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; getopts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hf:v&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; opt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$opt&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; in
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; h&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; show_help ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; f&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; FILE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$OPTARG&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; v&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; VERBOSE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;esac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Handle ? for unknown options&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; getopts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hf:v&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; opt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$opt&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; in
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; h&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; show_help ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; f&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; FILE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$OPTARG&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; v&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; VERBOSE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ?&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Invalid option: -&lt;/span&gt;$OPTARG&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;esac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="2-define-complete-optstring"&gt;2. Define complete optstring&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Include all valid options&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;getopts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hf:vo:q&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; opt
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# h = help flag&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# f = file (requires arg)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# v = verbose flag&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# o = output (requires arg)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# q = quiet flag&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="3-use---for-silent-error-handling"&gt;3. Use - for silent error handling&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: Suppress getopts error messages&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; getopts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;hf:v&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; opt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$opt&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; in
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; h&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; show_help ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; f&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; FILE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$OPTARG&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; v&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; VERBOSE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; :&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Option -&lt;/span&gt;$OPTARG&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt; requires an argument&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; ?&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Unknown option: -&lt;/span&gt;$OPTARG&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;esac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="4-support-long-options-with-manual-parsing"&gt;4. Support long options with manual parsing&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# CORRECT: For long options, parse before getopts&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; $# -gt &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;0&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; in
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; --help&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; show_help; shift ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; --file&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; FILE&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$2&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; shift &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; -*&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Unknown option: &lt;/span&gt;$1&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;; exit &lt;span style="color:#ae81ff"&gt;1&lt;/span&gt; ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; *&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; break ;;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;esac&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;done&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Then use getopts for short options&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="too-many-arguments"&gt;Too Many Arguments&lt;/a&gt; — argument limits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="bash-shift-error"&gt;Bash Shift Error&lt;/a&gt; — shift out of range&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="command-not-found"&gt;Command Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — missing commands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>[Solution] Bash Illegal Option Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/illegal-option/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/illegal-option/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-illegal-option-error-fix"&gt;Bash Illegal Option Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when a command or Bash builtin receives an option flag it doesn&amp;rsquo;t recognize.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Commands and builtins accept specific option flags. When you pass an unsupported option — due to a typo, wrong command, or version mismatch — the command rejects it with &amp;ldquo;illegal option.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Typo in option flag&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;ls -lal&lt;/code&gt; is fine, but &lt;code&gt;ls -llal&lt;/code&gt; is not.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;GNU vs BSD differences&lt;/strong&gt; — macOS &lt;code&gt;grep&lt;/code&gt; doesn&amp;rsquo;t support &lt;code&gt;-P&lt;/code&gt; (Perl regex).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing colon in getopts&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;getopts &amp;quot;abc&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; vs &lt;code&gt;getopts &amp;quot;a:bc&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using a flag not supported by the command version&lt;/strong&gt; — older versions lack newer flags.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-check-the-commands-help"&gt;Fix 1: Check the command&amp;rsquo;s help&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;command --help
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# or&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;man command
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-verify-option-syntax"&gt;Fix 2: Verify option syntax&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — -r is recursive, but -R is not a valid combo on all systems&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -Rr /path
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Right&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -R /path
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-handle-platform-differences-in-scripts"&gt;Fix 3: Handle platform differences in scripts&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Detect OS for different flag syntax&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$OSTYPE&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;darwin&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;* &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# macOS (BSD)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sed -i &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;s/old/new/g&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Linux (GNU)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; sed -i &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;s/old/new/g&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt; file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-getopts-with-proper-syntax"&gt;Fix 4: Use getopts with proper syntax&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong — missing colon means &amp;#39;a&amp;#39; doesn&amp;#39;t take an argument&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; getopts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;abc&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; opt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Right — &amp;#39;a:&amp;#39; means &amp;#39;a&amp;#39; takes an argument&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;while&lt;/span&gt; getopts &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;a:bc&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; opt; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;do&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ grep -P &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;pattern&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;grep: illegal option -- P
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ ls -Z
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls: invalid option -- &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;Z&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ bash -xv script.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# If script.sh doesn&amp;#39;t have executable permission and you didn&amp;#39;t use bash&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
